      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that high-density zoning leads to gentrification is often overstated and rooted in a misunderstanding of the relationship between density and affordability. In reality, well-planned high-density development can actually increase the availability of affordable housing options by incorporating mixed-income units and community land trusts, which can help preserve the existing social fabric of the neighborhood. This is particularly true when local governments prioritize community engagement, affordable housing, and inclusive zoning policies.",
